==English==
===Etymology===
Derived from Latin ''recapitulatio, -onis'', from ''recapitulare'' (with English ''-ate''), from ''re-'' "again, back" + ''capitulum'' "chapter, section", diminuitive of ''caput, capitis'' "head"
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''recapitulation'''
#The brief recitement of the major points in a narrative, article, or book. Summary.
#{{musiv}} The third major section of a musical movement written in sonata form, representing thematic material that originally appeared in th exposition section.
#{{biology}} The reenactment of the embryonic development in evolution of the species.

